# MCP Server Secrets
#
# Create files in thoughts/.secrets/ with one credential value per file.
# These are referenced by opencode.json using {file:thoughts/.secrets/<name>}
# substitution and are gitignored — NEVER commit actual secrets.
#
# Each file contains a single value, no quotes, no trailing newline.
#
# Example files to create:
#
#   thoughts/.secrets/atlassian-email         → CHANGE-ME@example.com
#   thoughts/.secrets/atlassian-api-token     → CHANGE-ME-ATLASSIAN-TOKEN
#   thoughts/.secrets/kibana-url              → https://CHANGE-ME.example.com
#   thoughts/.secrets/kibana-api-key          → CHANGE-ME-KIBANA-KEY
#   thoughts/.secrets/magento-url             → https://CHANGE-ME.example.com
#   thoughts/.secrets/magento-token           → CHANGE-ME-MAGENTO-TOKEN
#
# Quick setup (replace CHANGE-ME values with your actual credentials):
#
#   echo -n "CHANGE-ME@example.com"       > thoughts/.secrets/atlassian-email
#   echo -n "CHANGE-ME-ATLASSIAN-TOKEN"   > thoughts/.secrets/atlassian-api-token
#
# The -n flag avoids a trailing newline, which is important for tokens.
